caption:
This photograph is an aerial view of a lush, rural landscape characterized by a mix of verdant forested areas, open fields, and residential properties. The image captures the essence of a serene, countryside setting, possibly a farming community. 

The central focus of the picture is a straight road that cuts through the landscape from the foreground to the middle ground, bordered by several small houses or farm structures with varying roof colors such as red, white, and blue. These buildings are interspersed among fields that show different shades of green and brown, indicating various stages of cultivation or different types of crops.

To the left side of the image, dense forests dominate, with their dark green tones suggesting a mix of mature trees. In contrast, open fields predominantly occupy the right side, reflecting an agricultural use of the land. Temporary patches of forests or groups of trees sporadically break the continuity of the fields.

In the background, the landscape gently slopes towards a large body of water, visible at the upper right corner of the photograph. This adds a scenic view to the overall composition. The horizon is a blur of land and water, possibly a coastline, with the edges softened by distance and atmospheric perspective.

Shadows cast across the terrain indicate that the photograph was taken in the early morning or late afternoon when the sun is lower in the sky, enhancing the textures and contours of the landscape. The overall tranquility and the rural setting suggest a peaceful community closely connected with nature.
title: Aerial view of the central valley quadrangle which is bounded by tracyton, illahee, brownsville and silverdale.  These communities and others in the area will be affected by population growth when the navy's proposed trident submarine base is built nearby
